The paper deals with generating a shared secret key from motion data, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of accelerometer sensors and feature extraction from the data also falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD). The application of motion-based key generation for device pairing involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the quantization procedure, which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of mobile devices and their sensors suggests the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
